7/ What is the point of Destablecoin if there is a risk of deppeging? ⚖️

🔸 It is not more or less prone to de-pegging or de-stabilizing than stablecoins. 

🔸 Privileges of stablecoins & ability to be borderless and permissionless

🔸 Greater focus when building such ecosystems

6/ Why “Destablecoin” it may confuse new users to believe “unstable” instead? 🤝

🔸 Prefix “de” is important to acknowledge the progress & aim of Helio to be fully decentralized  

🔸 We recognize the confusion but we are committed to educating and pushing the ethos of DeFi

5/ Why “Destablecoin”? ⚡️

🔸 “De” for decentralized, marks the importance of this industry one we aim to be in 

🔸 Due to past project's failure in transparency it demonized “stablecoins”, leading investors to question its faith

🔸 Signals risk & encourages a responsible trade

4/ Difference between Destablecoin & Stablecoin? 👀

🔸 Decentralized assets as collateral 

🔸 Leverage on liquid staked assets

🔸 Accepts market fluctuations as a norm & not absolute stability at all costs

🔸 Aims for broad stability without an absolute peg to a fiat currency https://t.co/sAszy9AAqb

3/ What is the similarity between Destablecoin and Stablecoin? 💭

🔸 Destablecoins will utilize the overcollateralized model backed by crypto e.g. DAI.

2/ What is Destablecoin? 🤔

🔸 Destablecoins use liquid staking, 

🔸 Destablecoins utilize decentralized, liquid staked, crypto assets only as collateral 

🔸 Do not aim to achieve absolute price stability with fiat-based Stablecoins.
